<title>JAPAN: Prosecutors arrest former IBM Japan unit official.</title>
<headline>Prosecutors arrest former IBM Japan unit official.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Yokohama Prosecutors' Office said on Tuesday that it had arrested a former director of an IBM Japan Ltd subsidiary and two others for suspected breach of trust.</p>
<p>IBM Japan is a unit of International Business Machines Corp.</p>
<p>The prosecutors said that the three, including former director Nobuyoshi Okayasu, were suspected of embezzling a total of 22.19 million yen from the IBM Japan unit.</p>
<p>A spokesman for IBM Japan said the subsidiary filed a complaint with the prosecutors' office in 1994 against the former director for alleged breach of trust.</p>
<p>He declined to comment further.</p>
